You have two main ways to handle this:

1. **Make the enum public**: This is the most straightforward approach if you can allow the enum to be visible outside the assembly.

```csharp
public enum StyleType
{
    TextCss,
    TextJs
}
```

2. **Expose the value as an int**: If you must keep the enum `internal`, you can make the property using the enum `internal` as well, and provide a `public` property that casts the enum to an `int`.

```csharp
public class Style : VisionItem, BaseItem
{
    public string TargetType { get; set; }
    public string FontFamily { get; set; }
    public int FontSize { get; set; }

    internal StyleType Type { get; set; }

    public int TypeAsInt
    {
        get { return (int)Type; }
        set { Type = (StyleType)value; }
    }
}

internal enum StyleType
{
    TextCss,
    TextJs
}
```

This allows the `Style` class to remain public and the `StyleType` enum to remain internal, while still providing a way for external code to get or set the value via an integer.")
