Thought: The user is experiencing a SyntaxError when trying to call a private class field (#method2) as a static method. I need to investigate the difference between TypeScript's `private` modifier and JavaScript's hard-private `#` fields, and why the latter cannot be accessed via `@ts-ignore` or casting in the same way. I'll create a reproduction script to confirm the behavior.
<code>
content = """
