Thought: I need to translate the Python GCD and LCM functions into C# syntax. C# is statically typed and does not support tuple unpacking for swapping variables in the same way Python does, so I will need to use a temporary variable for the GCD loop. I'll write the code to a file first to ensure it's clean, although the user just wants the adaptation.
<code>
code = """public static int GCD(int a, int b)
{
    // Calculate the Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) using the Euclidean algorithm.
    // Constraints: 1 <= a, b <= 10^6
    // Example: GCD(4, 5) should return 1
    // Example: GCD(6, 14) should return 2
    while (b != 0)
    {
        int temp = b;
        b = a % b;
        a = temp;
    }
    return a;
}

public static int LCM(int a, int b)
{
    // Calculate the Least Common Multiple (LCM).
    // Constraints: 1 <= a, b <= 10^6
    // Example: LCM(4, 5) should return 20
    // Example: LCM(6, 14) should return 42
    return a * b / GCD(a, b);
}"""
